title: Abstention by far-right in Azores raises hopes for Portugal's new government
description: Portugal's far-right Chega party abstained on Friday from voting on the Social Democratic Party's (PSD) minority government policy programme in the Azores islands, thereby letting it pass, a move PSD hopes Chega will replicate nationwide after last weekend's inconclusive election.

title: Aid ship reaches Gaza coast; Israel rejects Hamas truce offer
description: The first ship carrying food aid reached the coast of the Gaza Strip on Friday, where hopes for a ceasefire to rescue the population from starvation suffered a new blow after Israel rejected the latest truce counter-proposal from Hamas.

title: Aid supply ship from Cyprus reaches Gaza coast
description: A ship towing a barge loaded with food arrived off Gaza on Friday, witnesses said, as a test run for a new aid route by sea from Cyprus into the devastated Palestinian enclave where famine looms after five months of Israel's military campaign.

title: At least 34 migrants missing off Tunisia, two die after boat sinks
description: At least 34 migrants were missing and two died after their boat sank off Tunisia as they tried to cross the Mediterranean to Italy, the Tunisian national guard said on Friday.

title: At least 8 dead after migrant boat sinks off Turkey, state media says
description: At least eight people drowned when a rubber boat carrying migrants sunk off Turkey's northwest province of Canakkale, the state-run Anadolu news agency reported on Friday.

title: Australia to resume funding to UN's main Palestinian relief agency
description: Australia will resume funding to the United Nations' main Palestinian relief agency, Foreign Minister Penny Wong said on Friday, almost two months after it paused ties over allegations some of the agency's employees participated in the Oct.7 Hamas attack.

title: Beirut says French plan for Lebanon-Israel truce could be 'step' to stability
description: Lebanon sees a French proposal meant to end hostilities with Israel and settle a border dispute as a possible "significant step" towards peace, according to a letter by Lebanon's foreign ministry dated Friday and seen by Reuters.

title: Belgorod, the city where the war in Ukraine came to Russia
description: Air raid sirens wail almost daily in the southern Russian city of Belgorod, sending people rushing for cover and reminding residents the full-scale war in neighbouring Ukraine is a reality for them too.

title: Biden denounces resurgence of Islamophobia amid Gaza war
description: U.S. President Joe Biden condemned on Friday what he called an ugly resurgence of Islamophobia since the Oct. 7 start of the Israel-Gaza war.

title: Biden says Schumer's concerns on Israel shared by many Americans
description: President Joe Biden said on Friday that U.S. Senator Chuck Schumer echoed the concerns of many Americans when he called for new elections in Israel and harshly criticized Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu as an obstacle to peace.

title: Black voters less swayed by Biden's message that Trump threatens democracy, poll shows
description: One of U.S. President Joe Biden's key campaign messages, that Donald Trump is a threat to democracy, is winning over fewer Black supporters and those without college degrees than other segments of his political base, a Reuters/Ipsos poll found.

title: Blinken calls for closer global cooperation on tackling synthetic drugs
description: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken on Friday called for greater international cooperation to fight the booming trafficking of illicit synthetic drugs such as fentanyl, the leading cause of overdose deaths in his country.

title: Brazil eyes exports via China-controlled Chancay port, Peruvian minister says
description: Brazil is interested in exporting soy, corn and other products through Peru's China-controlled Chancay port, Peruvian Economy Minister Jose Arista said on Thursday, according to state news agency Andina.

title: Bulgarians pay last respects to Orthodox Patriarch Neophyte
description: Bulgarian worshippers thronged Sofia's golden-domed Alexander Nevsky Cathedral on Friday to pay their last respects to Orthodox Christian Patriarch Neophyte who died this week aged 78.

title: Canada's Trudeau says he often mulls quitting his 'crazy job,' but will stay on
description: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau, whose Liberals are trailing badly in the polls, on Friday said he thought about quitting his "crazy job" every day but insisted he would stay in office until the next election.

title: China's Xi willing to work with Angola as it moves on from oil
description: Chinese President Xi Jinping said he would support Chinese firms that invest in Angola's agriculture and manufacturing sectors, state media reported on Friday, as the African oil producing nation seeks help in diversifying its economy.

title: Congo lifts moratorium on death penalty, justice ministry circular shows
description: Democratic Republic Congo has lifted a moratorium on the death penalty, citing treachery and espionage in recurring armed conflicts as the reason for allowing a resumption of executions, said a justice ministry circular seen by Reuters on Friday.

title: Croatian president to run for more powerful PM's post in April election
description: Croatian President Zoran Milanovic on Friday set April 17 for a parliamentary election and said he would run for the more powerful post of prime minister after dissolving parliament in the small European Union country.

title: Egypt is striving to secure a ceasefire in Gaza, Sisi says
description: Egypt is seeking to reach a deal for a ceasefire in Gaza, increase entry of aid and to allow displaced people in the south of the enclave to move to the north, President Abdel Fattah al-Sisi said on Friday.

title: EU close to sanctioning violent Israeli settlers - diplomats
description: The European Union is close to agreeing sanctions on Israeli settlers attacking Palestinians in the West Bank after Hungary signalled an end to its opposition, European diplomats said on Friday.

title: EU plan to ease farmers' fallow land requirement stalls on detail
description: European policymakers' plan to replace a requirement for farmers to leave land fallow with a voluntary scheme has been held up by disagreement on details, the agriculture commissioner said on Friday on a visit to Warsaw.

title: EU set to agree new Russia sanctions over Navalny's death
description: The European Union is set to agree sanctions on several people seen as involved in the mistreatment and death of Kremlin critic Alexei Navalny in an Arctic penal colony, three diplomats said on Friday.

title: Exclusive: Hamas issues ceasefire proposal detailing exchange of hostages, prisoners
description: Hamas has presented a Gaza ceasefire proposal to mediators and the U.S. which includes the release of Israeli hostages in exchange for freedom for Palestinian prisoners, 100 of whom are serving life sentences, according to a proposal seen by Reuters.

title: Finland could block asylum seekers from entering via Russia
description: Finland plans to adopt temporary legislation that will allow the country's border authorities to block asylum seekers arriving via Russia from entering the Nordic nation, Interior Minister Mari Rantanen and Prime Minister Petteri Orpo said on Friday.

title: Former Brazil military chiefs implicate Bolsonaro in coup conspiracy
description: The former commanders of Brazil's Army and Air Force told police investigators that President Jair Bolsonaro summoned them twice to meetings to discuss a possible coup d'état after his election defeat in 2022, according to their testimonies released on Friday by the Supreme Court.

title: France's Macron: Europe's security at stake in Ukraine
description: French President Emmanuel Macron said on Friday that France and its allies will continue to support Ukraine as long as it takes.

title: G7 warns Iran not to give Russia ballistic missiles for Ukraine war
description: The Group of Seven (G7) industrialised powers told Iran on Friday not to transfer ballistic missiles to Russia to use in its conflict with Ukraine, warning that they would take action against Tehran if it did so.

title: Hamas lashes out at Abbas's 'unilateral' designation of new PM
description: The Islamist group Hamas on Friday criticized the "unilateral" designation by Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas of an ally and leading business figure as prime minister with a mandate to help reform the Palestinian Authority (PA) and rebuild Gaza.

title: Hamas says it presents comprehensive vision of truce deal to mediators
description: Palestinian Islamist group Hamas said on Thursday it presented to mediators a comprehensive vision of a truce deal that is based on stopping the Israeli "aggression" against Palestinians in the Gaza Strip, providing relief and aid, the return of displaced Gazans to their houses, and the withdrawal of Israeli forces.

title: Hezbollah tells Iran it would fight alone in any war with Israel
description: With ally Hamas under attack in Gaza, the head of Iran's Quds Force visited Beirut in February to discuss the risk posed if Israel next aims at Lebanon's Hezbollah, an offensive that could severely hurt Tehran's main regional partner, seven sources said.

title: Hungary's Orban ready to 'occupy' Brussels to bring EU change
description: Hungary's Prime Minister Viktor Orban said on Friday he was ready to march to Brussels and "occupy" the European Union's centre in order to "defend Hungary's freedom and sovereignty", ahead of European Parliament elections later this year.

title: Hunters in Niger lament loss of range to Islamist threat
description: Hunting for small game is a traditional pursuit across the vast sandy steppes in West Africa's Sahel region, but rising violence linked to a decade-old fight with Islamist insurgents has limited the range for hunters in Niger like Abdou Kouda.

title: In Gaza, Palestinians hold Ramadan prayers by ruins of mosque
description: Palestinians in Gaza held the first Friday prayers of Ramadan outside the ruins of a mosque levelled in Israel's offensive, one of hundreds the Hamas-run authorities say have been damaged or destroyed in Israeli attacks since October.

title: In Ukraine's bombarded ports, ship buyers scout for deals
description: Since Russia invaded Ukraine two years ago, nearly 50 merchant ships have been languishing in its waters, stuck in ports too dangerous to sail from.

title: Independent vote monitor says Russian elections are 'most secret' ever
description: The head of an independent vote-monitoring group that Russia has labelled a "foreign agent" says the presidential election that began on Friday and is widely expected to re-elect Vladimir Putin is the least transparent the country has seen.

title: India dismisses U.S. concern about its citizenship law as 'misplaced'
description: Comments by the United States expressing concern about India's implementation of a contentious citizenship law based on religion are "misplaced, misinformed, and unwarranted", the foreign ministry of the South Asian nation said on Friday.

title: India minister says party funding system needs transparency
description: Indian Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman said on Friday a political funding mechanism scrapped by the Supreme Court as "unconstitutional" was an improvement on the past but a more transparent system should be put in place.

title: India's Election Commission to announce dates for general elections on March 16
description: India's election panel said on Friday it would announce dates for general elections at 3 p.m. local time (0930 GMT) on March 16.

title: Iran Air could be banned from Europe if Tehran sends missiles to Russia, US warns
description: G7 nations are prepared to respond with severe new penalties that could include a ban on Iran Air flights to Europe if Iran proceeds with the transfer of close-range ballistic missiles to Russia, a senior U.S. official said on Friday.

title: Israeli military says troops did not open fire on Gazans waiting for aid
description: Israel's military said armed Palestinians had opened fire while crowds were waiting for aid trucks in the northern Gaza Strip and denied soldiers fired at the convoy, defending its actions in an incident on Thursday in which Gaza officials said 21 people were killed.

title: Japan military helicopter crashes in Oita prefecture, media reports
description: A Japanese Self-Defence Forces' helicopter crashed in the country's southern prefecture of Oita, a local TV broadcaster reported on Friday.

title: Joe Biden to meet Irish PM amid anger over war in Gaza
description: U.S. President Joe Biden will host Irish Prime Minister Leo Varadkar on Friday for the annual St. Patrick's Day reception at the White House, even as a portion of the usual Irish delegation boycotts the event over Biden's handling of the war in Gaza.

title: Kremlin says U.S. is conducting a covert influence campaign against Russia
description: The Kremlin on Friday said that the United States has been trying to conduct a covert influence campaign against the Russian authorities, but that Moscow's security services had taken action to minimise its impact.

title: Marine organisation reports missiles flying over ship near Yemen's al Hudaydah
description: The United Kingdom Maritime Trade Operations (UKMTO) organisation said early on Friday that it had received a report that missiles passed near a ship 50 nautical miles (93 km) southwest of al Hudaydah, Yemen.

title: Mexico City mayoral race tightens on anger over water shortages
description: Just a few months ago ruling party candidate Clara Brugada looked like a shoo-in to be elected the next mayor of Mexico City. But a worsening water crisis has many voters rethinking their choice to run Mexico's largest and most important city.

title: Most of the parties for Haiti's transition council have named representatives, Blinken says
description: Most of the parties for Haiti's transition council have named their representative but a couple still have yet to do so, U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken said on Friday, as the Caribbean nation faces a political and humanitarian crisis.

title: New Zealand warns of 'significantly slower' growth over next few years
description: New Zealand will report "significantly slower" economic growth for the next few years when it releases a pre-Budget update in two weeks' time, Finance Minister Nicola Willis said on Friday, as slower productivity growth hampers the country's economy.

title: 'Noon against Putin': Opposition urges Russians to fulfil Navalny's 'last wish'
description: With Alexei Navalny dead and buried in a Moscow graveyard and other anti-Kremlin politicians in exile or jailed, Russia's opposition is at a low ebb. But on Sunday, as Russians go to the polls, opponents of President Vladimir Putin will stage a symbolic protest they hope will resonate.

title: North Korean defectors seek more U.N. monitoring of abuses
description: North Koreans defectors spoke at a U.N. event in Geneva on Friday to expose human rights violations in a country one of them described as "hell" and to advocate for a strengthened U.N. mandate to investigate and document them.

title: Polish opposition leader refuses to tell all to phone-hacking commission
description: The leader of Poland's largest opposition party said on Friday he would refuse to tell everything he knows to a parliamentary commission investigating allegations of phone-hacking when his party was in power.

title: Pope Francis reflects on his life and mortality in memoir
description: Pope Francis, at 87 increasingly weak and wobbly, takes a trip down memory lane and speaks of his hopes for the Roman Catholic Church's future in a new book reflecting on his life and its intersection with major world events.

title: Portugal pledges $109 million to Czech scheme on ammunition for Ukraine
description: Portugal will contribute 100 million euros ($109 million) to a Czech-led initiative seeking to deliver ammunition to Ukraine from third nations, the country's defence ministry said.

title: Putin is master of all he surveys as Russians head to polls
description: In a Russia at war, there is only one real candidate and only one winner: Vladimir Putin.

title: Putin on brink of six more years in power as Russians vote
description: Russia began three days of voting on Friday in an presidential election that is set to extend the rule of Vladimir Putin by six more years.

title: Putin says Ukraine will be punished for election day attacks on civilians
description: President Vladimir Putin said on Friday that Ukraine would be punished for trying to disrupt the Russian presidential election by shelling civilian targets in Russian territory and using 2,500 armed soldiers to try to pierce Russia's borders.

title: Russia launches criminal case against woman who poured liquid into ballot box
description: Russian state investigators in Moscow said on Friday they had opened a criminal case against a woman who poured liquid into a ballot box.

title: Russia says it repelled attempted Ukrainian cross-border incursion on Thursday
description: Russia's defence ministry said on Friday that its forces had thwarted a Ukrainian attempt to launch a cross-border attack on Russia's Belgorod region on Thursday.

title: Russia says it shot down seven Ukraine-launched missiles over Belgorod region
description: Russian air defence systems shot down seven Vampire missiles launched by Ukraine at Russia's Belgorod region, Russian Defence Ministry said in a statement on Friday.

title: Russia systematically tortures Ukraine POWs, UN commission says
description: A United Nations commission of inquiry on Ukraine said on Friday that it had gathered more evidence that Russia has systematically tortured Ukrainian prisoners of war, documenting rape threats and the use of electric shocks on genitals.

title: Russian ambassador to Washington says embassy has received threats over election
description: Russia's ambassador to the United States said on Thursday his embassy had received a number of threats in connection with the Russian presidential election this week.

title: Russian missile attack kills two in Ukraine's Odesa, governor says
description: A Russian missile attack on Ukraine's southern city of Odesa on Friday killed at least two people and wounded others, the regional governor said.

title: Russian national detained in Moscow for launching drones for Ukraine
description: Russia's Federal Security Service (FSB) said on Friday that a Russian national had been detained in Moscow on suspicion of treason and had confessed to assembling and launching drones on behalf of Ukraine.

title: Russian rights group says jailed leader, 70, was asked to fight in Ukraine war
description: Jailed Russian human rights activist Oleg Orlov was asked to sign a form saying he was willing to fight in Ukraine despite the fact he is 70, his organisation said on Friday.

title: Scholz, Macron and Tusk seek to bridge European divisions on Ukraine
description: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz will host his French and Polish counterparts in Berlin on Friday in a bid to project European unity on support for Ukraine after weeks of friction between the allies.

title: Senegal releases opposition leader Sonko, presidential candidate Faye from prison, state TV says
description: Senegalese opposition firebrand Ousmane Sonko and the presidential candidate he is backing in the March 24 election, Bassirou Diomaye Faye, were released from prison on Thursday, state broadcaster RTS said on its website.

title: Senegal Supreme Court rejects opposition party bid to halt presidential election
description: Senegal's Supreme Court on Friday rejected a bid by one of the main opposition parties to halt a presidential election on March 24, sparing the country from another constitutional crisis.

title: Shipping group CMA CGM to halt calls at Haiti's Port au Prince
description: French shipping group CMA CGM said on Friday it was suspending its calls at Port au Prince due to the worsening security situation in the Haitian capital.

title: Somali security forces 'neutralize' hotel attackers, national TV says
description: Somali security forces have "neutralized" those who attacked a popular hotel in the capital Mogadishu, Somali National Television said on social media platform X on Friday.

title: South Korea police raid Korea Aerospace office over suspected fighter jet tech leak
description: South Korean police raided the head office of Korea Aerospace Industries (KAI) on Friday in connection with two Indonesian nationals accused of leaking technology related to a fighter jet project, a police official said.

title: South Korea to host third democracy summit with digital threats on agenda
description: South Korea is poised to host the third Summit for Democracy next week, taking up a U.S.-led initiative aimed at discussing ways to stop democratic backsliding and erosion of rights and freedoms worldwide.

title: Thailand's flourishing cannabis culture to end as government seeks ban
description: Thodsapol Hongtong is enjoying a smoke with his friends at the "Green Party", a venue where recreational cannabis enthusiasts meet in the Thai capital Bangkok to chat and have a good time. But it's a pastime that may be coming to an end.

title: Tokyo's controversial Yasukuni Shrine picks ex-admiral as chief priest
description: Japan's Yasukuni Shrine has picked a former military commander as its chief priest in a move that could stir controversy over a site that other Asian nations see as a symbol of Japan's wartime aggression.

title: Twice displaced, Crimean Tatar woman longs for home 10 years after annexation
description: Lierane has fled Russian invaders twice in the last decade but remains hopeful that she will one day return to her native Crimea, the Ukrainian peninsula seized by Moscow in 2014.

title: Two killed in latest Russian drone attack on Ukraine
description: Two people were killed after Russia unleashed its second overnight mass drone attack on Ukraine in two days, authorities in Ukraine said on Friday.

title: Ukraine official: two Russian border regions are now active combat zones
description: A senior Ukrainian intelligence official said on Thursday that armed groups he described as Russians opposed to the Kremlin were pressing an incursion into Russian territory and had turned two border regions into "active combat zones".

title: Ukraine urges poor nations to protect citizens from Russian recruitment
description: Ukraine urged Global South countries on Friday to do more to prevent their citizens from being recruited to fight for Russia in its war on Ukraine, presenting to the public what it said were eight prisoners of war from such countries.

title: Ukrainian authorities launch mass evacuation in northern region
description: Ukrainian authorities have begun mass evacuations of communities in the country's northern Sumy region close to the Russian border after extended periods of intense shelling of the area, local officials said on Friday.

title: Ukrainian drones attack Russian oil refinery in Kaluga region - source
description: Ukraine attacked a small oil refinery in Russia's Kaluga region with drones early on Friday, causing damage in an operation that was conducted by the GUR military spy agency, a Ukrainian intelligence source told Reuters.

title: UN chief condemns Russia bid to hold presidential poll in occupied Ukraine
description: Secretary-General Antonio Guterres has condemned Russian efforts to conduct its presidential election in occupied areas of Ukraine, a U.N spokesperson said on Friday.

title: UN warns of catastrophic hunger in Sudan in coming months
description: Nearly five million people in Sudan could suffer catastrophic hunger in parts of the war-torn country in the coming months, United Nations aid chief Martin Griffiths warned the Security Council on Friday in a note seen by Reuters.

title: UNICEF warns of catastrophic loss of lives in Sudan as famine looms
description: The U.N. children's agency warned on Friday of a potential catastrophic loss of lives in Sudan as the civil war worsens hunger and called for a massive mobilisation of resources.

title: US aid chief to announce $25 million in humanitarian assistance for Haiti
description: U.S. aid chief Samantha Power is set to announce $25 million in humanitarian assistance for Haiti on Friday, according to a statement seen by Reuters in advance, as the Caribbean nation faces a long-running political and humanitarian crisis.

title: U.S. commandos train for the unexpected in North Korea's shadow
description: U.S. special operations troops in South Korea are training and preparing for unexpected threats at a time when global crises are more interconnected than ever, their commander said during an exercise this week.

title: US lawmakers blocking critical funding for Haiti multinational mission
description: U.S. lawmakers are refusing to release millions of dollars in funding that Washington views as critical to help tackle spiraling violence in Haiti, in another potential stumbling block for the international force.

title: US working to bridge gaps on Gaza hostage deal, says Blinken
description: The United States is working intensively with Israel and intermediaries Qatar and Egypt to bridge remaining gaps for a hostage deal that would see a pause in fighting between Israel and Hamas, U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken said on Friday.

title: Vessel was reportedly targeted near Yemen's Hodeidah, Ambrey and UKMTO say
description: British maritime security firm Ambrey and the United Kingdom Maritime Trade Operations (UKMTO) reported on Friday an incident near Yemen's Hodeidah where the Iran-aligned Houthis continue to attack shipping lanes in solidarity with Palestinians in the Gaza war.

title: World Court to hear Nicaragua-Germany dispute over Israel aid in April
description: The International Court of Justice on Friday said it would hold hearings on April 8 and 9 in Nicaragua's case against Germany for giving military aid to Israel and defunding the U.N. Palestinian refugee agency (UNRWA).
